Title: All Eyez on Me Trailer #1 (2017) | Movieclips Trailers
Comment:
(SPOILER ALERT)




I didn't like the ending because the last scene is of him getting shot and the police taking him out of the vehicle. There was no follow-up whatsoever, even though he died in the hospital 5-6 days later in reality. There should have been a scene of his girlfriend finding out he got shot, because in the movie, he chooses to go to the club with Suge, despite his girlfriend being worried about him. It made no sense to create that scene whatsoever, because that's the last time you see her in the movie. There isn't even a scene of her finding out he was shot in the first place. The movie should've had a hospital scene where family and Death Row members visited 2Pac while he was in a coma. I believe there's an interview with Snoop Dogg where he says he visited Pac in the hospital and started talking to him because he felt that he could hear him, even though he was out cold. This should have been in the movie. It would've been more emotional, and in my opinion, way better than just the screen going dark right after he gets capped. That's just my two cents though.

Other than the ending, which was mediocre at best I feel, the movie definitely is worth watching. I enjoyed it, and it gave me insight to how rich but tragic life was for a 90's rapper that just wanted to make a change.

Comment:
The movie was sloppy. Seemed scripted which is no a good thing. It didn't make it feel like it wasn't a movie. It felt like drama class. The actor who looks like Pac did a good job, but the script sucked. Where is his best friend? Where is the security guard that also was his friend?

They could have used much better material like 2Pac and Biggie beef. 2Pac wanting to run for politics.

They rushed this movie and squeezed everything into small portions which is stupid. The Snoop scene was little information. What happened to Dre? it was a clip less than a second. 

The beef with Biggie seemed too short. The beginning took too long on his mom. It just was too draining. They should have used the same clip from Biggies movie where its the opposite of that moivie. Show Biggie getting arrested.

This movie is not representing Pac correctly.

5.5/10

Comment:
The movie really didn't live up to the hype; it's rushed and either clumsily or lazily directed, and tries so hard to include every single aspect of 2pac's life rather than finding an angle and main focus. The film also never gives the audience the chance to let the conflicts, environments, and moods get established and sink in since most scenes, events, and conflicts that take place before 1995 last for about 1-2 minutes.

Not to mention that the raps included feel like they are there just to please the audience rather than having a significance for the story, and that's because their background and motivationd aren't explored properly.

After this movie, Someone needs to make a movie about the East vs West Coast Event. I feel that people need to understand that the whole east coast west coast feud was a big media thing and to show what was really¬†going behind the scenes from all¬†important/ critical¬†vantage points.¬†I mean yes people can do more research on the internet but¬†in this modern age what better way then to put it in a movie to inflict interest of a situation¬†to an audience, influencing them to go and do more of their own research. It was a big event just like the Rodney king trials, O.J. Simpson trials, L.A. Riots, Police brutality back in the 80s-90s, etc. 
I mean look at the show, "American Crime Story: The People v. O.J. Simpson", I was alive during that time yet I paid no attention to it but I heard about it and knew alittle about what it was, yet I never took interest in it until the show came out and when I started seeing how the show was a big deal on media, before I watched the show myself I did my research first and watched the whole trial on YouTube and watched the first movie that came out about O.J. Simpson and then I watched the show and saw the things that were happening behind the scenes that you didn't get to see in the news¬†unless you were actually there. Yes a few things were off in the show but the concept and idea and knowledge on the bit of American history was very educational to me and made me see things from a different light. That's why I feel they should make these movies for the younger generation.
